ool/required/default |\n| Logging | `github.com/rs/zerolog` | Structured JSON di prod, console di dev |\n| UUID v4 | `github.com/google/uuid` | — |\n| Testing | stdlib `testing` + table-driven (per `/golang-testing` skill) | TDD untuk pure functions, integration via `app.Test()` |\n| Container | Multi-stage: `golang:1.26-alpine` builder → `gcr.io/distroless/static-debian12:nonroot` runtime | ~15-20MB image, no shell, non-root |\n| CI | GitHub Actions | golangci-lint v2.12.2 (via action @v7) + race-tests + docker build |\n| Linter | golangci-lint v2 | `.golangci.yml` schema v2 |\n| JSON encoder | `github.com/bytedance/sonic` | Fiber-recommended fastest alternative — JIT-based, ~5-10× stdlib; configured via `fiber.Config{JSONEncoder, JSONDecoder}` |\n\n## High-Performance Fiber Notes (verified via Context7 `/websites/gofiber_io_next`)\n\n- **`Immutable: false`** (default) → zero-allocation handlers. Jangan reference `fiber.Ctx` values setelah handler returns; copy bytes kalau perlu persist.\n- **Fiber `client` package** untuk outbound HTTP → wraps `fasthttp.HostClient` dengan reusable connection pool. Lebih cepat daripada stdlib `net/http` untuk volume tinggi.\n- **Context pool** managed by framework (acquired on request, released after) → minimize GC.\n\n## Project Structure (package-by-domain, Ben Johnson \"Standard Package Layout\")\n\n```\nservices/checkout-url/\n├── cmd/server/\n│   └── main.go                # entry: config → logger → midtrans client → app → listen + graceful shutdown\n├── checkout/                  # DOMAIN package: types, business logic, consumer-defined interfaces\n│   ├── order.go               # Order, CheckoutRequest types\n│   ├── parser.go              # ParseQuery() — Meta Shops query → CheckoutRequest, ErrInvalidQuery\n│   ├── catalog.go             # Product, in-memory catalog, Lookup(), ErrProductNotFound\n│   ├── builder.go             # BuildPaymentLinkRequest() — compose Midtrans payload\n│   ├── client.go              # PaymentLinkClient interface (consumer-defined; midtrans pkg implements)\n│   └── *_test.go              # table-driven tests\n├── midtrans/                  # Midtrans HTTP client (depends on Fiber's fasthttp client)\n│   ├── client.go              # Client (implements checkout.PaymentLinkClient), CreatePaymentLink, Error\n│   └── client_test.go\n├── httpapi/                   # Fiber HTTP transport layer\n│   ├── server.go              # NewApp(cfg, log, client) *fiber.App — wires routes + middleware\n│   ├── checkout.go            # GET /checkout handler\n│   ├── health.go              # GET /health handler\n│   ├── error.go               # custom fiber.ErrorHandler — maps domain errors → HTTP responses\n│   └── server_test.go         # integration tests via app.Test() + mock checkout.PaymentLinkClient\n├── config/\n│   └── config.go              # env loader + Zod-style validation\n├── .env.example\n├── .dockerignore\n├── .golangci.yml\n├── Dockerfile\n├── go.mod\n└── README.md\n\n.github/workflows/checkout-url-ci.yml  # repo root: lint + test + docker-build\n```\n\n**Rationale (Ben Johnson \"Standard Package Layout\"):**\n\n- `checkout/` = domain root. Contains entity types + business logic + **interfaces it consumes** (e.g., `PaymentLinkClient`). No external deps (no Fiber, no Midtrans HTTP). Maximally testable.\n- `midtrans/` = dependency package. Implements `checkout.PaymentLinkClient`. Depends on Fiber's fasthttp client. Swappable.\n- `httpapi/` = transport layer. Knows about Fiber. Wires `checkout` domain to HTTP routes.\n- `config/` = configuration. Loaded once at startup.\n- **No `internal/handler/service/repo` layering** — over-abstraction untuk thin proxy service. Each package owns its concern.\n\n## Env Vars\n\n| Name | Required | Default | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `MIDTRANS_SERVER_KEY` | YES | — | Sandbox prefix `SB-Mid-server-` |\n| `MIDTRANS_CLIENT_KEY` | YES | — | — |\n| `MIDTRANS_MERCHANT_ID` | YES | — | — |\n| `MIDTRANS_API_BASE` | — | `https://api.sandbox.midtrans.com` | — |\n| `CUSTOMER_REQUIRED` | — | `true` | bool |\n| `ENABLED_PAYMENTS` | — | `other_qris` | CSV (envSeparator `,`) |\n| `EXPIRY_DURATION` | — | `15` | int |\n| `EXPIRY_UNIT` | — | `minutes` | enum: `minutes` / `hours` / `days` (plural) |\n| `PORT` | — | `8080` | int |\n| `LOG_LEVEL` | — | `info` | zerolog level |\n| `APP_ENV` | — | `development` | enum: `development` / `test` / `production` |\n| `RATE_LIMIT_PER_MIN` | — | `60` | int |\n\n`.env` di-gitignore, `.env.example` di-commit dengan dummy values.\n\n## Midtrans Spec Quirks (verified via sandbox testing)\n\n- **JANGAN kirim `customer_details` object**. Sandbox tolak empty/partial dengan 400 (\"Please fill in at least either email, phone or name in customer_details object\"). `customer_required: true` di top-level cukup — Midtrans render form di payment page, customer isi sendiri.\n- `expiry.unit` plural (`\"minutes\"` / `\"hours\"` / `\"days\"`)\n- `enabled_payments: [\"other_qris\"]` = generic QRIS (mendukung GoPay + ShopeePay QRIS)\n- `custom_field1/2/3` max 255 chars each — truncate `fbclid` di parser\n- Auth: `Authorization: Basic ` + base64(`SERVER_KEY` + `:`)\n- Response shape: `{ payment_url, order_id, payment_link_id, token, transaction_status }`\n\n## Phases\n\n### Phase 1 — Foundation\n- [ ] `go mod init`, install deps (Fiber v3, middleware/limiter, middleware/recover, middleware/requestid, zerolog, godotenv, caarlos0/env/v11, google/uuid, bytedance/sonic)\n- [ ] `config/config.go`: struct dengan env tags + `Load()` + manual validate untuk enum\n- [ ] zerolog setup (console writer di dev, JSON otherwise)\n- [ ] `.golangci.yml` v2 schema, `.env.example`, `.dockerignore`, README\n\n### Phase 2 — Domain (`checkout` package)\n- [ ] `Product`, `Order`, `CheckoutRequest` types; `ErrProductNotFound`, `ErrInvalidQuery` sentinels\n- [ ] `Lookup(productID)` — hardcoded catalog dict, 2+ products minimum\n- [ ] `ParseQuery(map[string]string) (CheckoutRequest, error)` — RFC 3986 decode, qty ≥ 1 integer, truncate fbclid ke 255 char\n- [ ] `BuildPaymentLinkRequest(req CheckoutRequest, cfg Config) (Payload, error)` — UUID order_id, sum gross_amount, item_details mapping, NO customer_details, env-driven tunables\n- [ ] `PaymentLinkClient` interface (consumer-defined, implemented by midtrans package)\n- [ ] Table-driven tests per `/golang-testing` skill — `t.Helper()`, `t.Cleanup()`, `t.Parallel()` where safe\n\n### Phase 3 — Midtrans client (`midtrans` package)\n- [ ] `Client` struct wraps `client.Client` from `github.com/gofiber/fiber/v3/client` (Fiber's fasthttp-based HTTP client)\n- [ ] `New(cfg) *Client` — set timeout 10s, Basic auth header, JSON content type. Marshal/unmarshal payload via `sonic.Marshal/Unmarshal` (konsisten dengan inbound)\n- [ ] `CreatePaymentLink(ctx, payload) (Response, error)` — POST to `/v1/payment-links`, retry 2x on 5xx/network errors (backoff 500ms, 1500ms), no retry on 4xx\n- [ ] `Error` struct dengan `StatusCode`, `ResponseBody`, `Cause` + `Unwrap()`\n- [ ] Implements `checkout.PaymentLinkClient` interface\n- [ ] Tests: mock via `fasthttp.HostClient` substitution OR via `httpapi`-level interface mock\n\n### Phase 4 — HTTP layer (`httpapi` package)\n- [ ] Health handler — `200 {\"status\":\"ok\"}`, no external calls\n- [ ] Checkout handler — `ParseQuery` → `BuildPaymentLinkRequest` → `client.CreatePaymentLink` → `c.Redirect().Status(302).To(...)`\n- [ ] Custom `fiber.ErrorHandler` — `errors.As` mapping: `ErrInvalidQuery` → 400, `ErrProductNotFound` → 400, `midtrans.Error` → 502, default → 500. Include `request_id` in all error bodies.\n- [ ] Request logger middleware — structured zerolog per request (skip log on error path — ErrorHandler logs sendiri dengan context lengkap)\n- [ ] Rate limiter (`middleware/limiter`) on `/checkout` only — `Max: cfg.RateLimitPerMin`, `Expiration: time.Minute`, IP-based KeyGenerator, custom LimitReached returning 429 + request_id\n- [ ] `NewApp(cfg, log, client) *fiber.App` factory — `fiber.New(fiber.Config{ErrorHandler: ..., JSONEncoder: sonic.Marshal, JSONDecoder: sonic.Unmarshal})`, set `TrustProxy` di production\n\n### Phase 5 — Entry + Integration\n- [ ] `cmd/server/main.go`: `config.Load()` → `logger.New()` → `midtrans.New()` → `httpapi.NewApp()` → goroutine `app.Listen(\":<PORT>\")`. Graceful shutdown on SIGINT/SIGTERM via `app.ShutdownWithContext(10s)`.\n- [ ] Integration tests (`httpapi/server_test.go`) via `app.Test()` dengan mocked `checkout.PaymentLinkClient`:\n  - Happy single + multi-item with custom fields → verify outgoing payload shape\n  - Auth header base64 correct\n  - Missing products → 400 invalid_query\n  - Unknown product → 400 product_not_found\n  - Midtrans 5xx (3x attempts) → 502\n  - Midtrans 4xx (no retry) → 502\n  - Rate limit (`RateLimitPerMin=2`, 3 reqs) → r3 = 429\n  - `/health` not rate-limited\n\n### Phase 6 — Packaging\n- [ ] Dockerfile multi-stage: `golang:1.26-alpine` builder (`CGO_ENABLED=0 go build -ldflags='-s -w'`) → `gcr.io/distroless/static-debian12:nonroot` runtime. `EXPOSE 8080`, `ENV APP_ENV=production`, `ENTRYPOINT [\"/checkout-url\"]`. No HEALTHCHECK (distroless = no shell; orchestrator hits `/health`).\n- [ ] CI workflow (`.github/workflows/checkout-url-ci.yml`): trigger on PR + push to main dengan path filter `services/checkout-url/**`. Jobs (working-directory `services/checkout-url`): lint (`golangci/golangci-lint-action@v7` + `version: v2.12.2`) + test (`go test -race -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./... ./...`) + docker-build (`docker/build-push-action@v6` push:false).\n\n## Testing Approach (per `/golang-testing` skill)\n\n- **TDD** untuk pure functions (parser, catalog, builder) — RED → GREEN → REFACTOR\n- **Table-driven tests** untuk input variation. Naming: `tt.name` describes scenario clearly\n- **Helper functions** via `t.Helper()` + `t.Cleanup()` untuk resource setup/teardown\n- **`t.Parallel()`** untuk independent tests (most unit tests)\n- **Integration tests** via Fiber's `app.Test(req, fiber.TestConfig{Timeout: 10*time.Second})` — bump timeout supaya retry path (3 attempts dengan backoff) bisa selesai\n- **Interface-based mocking** — define interface di consumer package (`checkout.PaymentLinkClient`), mock di tests\n- **Coverage target**: ≥ 80% via `go test -race -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./... ./...`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `go build ./...` + `go vet ./...` + `gofmt -l .` clean\n- [ ] `go test -race ./...` all pass; coverage ≥ 80%\n- [ ] `golangci-lint run ./...` clean\n- [ ] **Smoke E2E local** dengan sandbox key:\n  ```\n  curl -i \"http://localhost:8080/checkout?products=grw7y67xo5%3A1&coupon=ADHA2026&cart_origin=meta_shops&fbclid=abc123\"\n  ```\n  → `HTTP/1.1 302 Found` + `Location: https://app.sandbox.midtrans.com/payment-links/...`\n- [ ] **Browser test**: buka `Location` URL → render Midtrans payment page (customer form + QRIS option). Bayar QRIS via `https://simulator.sandbox.midtrans.com`. Verify success di `https://dashboard.sandbox.midtrans.com` + `custom_field1/2/3` populated benar.\n- [ ] **Health check**: `curl http://localhost:8080/health` → `200 {\"status\":\"ok\"}`\n- [ ] **Error cases**:\n  - `curl -i http://localhost:8080/checkout` → 400 `invalid_query` dengan `request_id`\n  - `curl -i http://localhost:8080/checkout?products=unknown%3A1` → 400 `product_not_found`\n- [ ] **Rate limit** (verified via integration test): spam ke `/checkout` melebihi `RATE_LIMIT_PER_MIN` → 429 dengan `request_id`. `/health` tidak ke-limit.\n- [ ] **Docker**: `docker build -t checkout-url .` sukses, image < 20MB, `docker run --env-file .env -p 8080:8080 checkout-url` boot, `/health` 200, container run as `nonroot`.\n- [ ] **CI**: PR → 3 checks (lint, test, docker-build) hijau dalam < 5 menit\n\n## Out of Scope (Future)\n\n- Persistent order storage (DB)\n- Midtrans webhook handler untuk update internal state\n- Production keys + production deploy infra\n- Customer-facing post-payment redirect (di-handle Midtrans Dashboard)\n- Dynamic catalog dari source eksternal\n- Analytics ingestion untuk `fbclid` / `utm_*`\n\n\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/blastcoid/dhianstore/issues/19/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/blastcoid/dhianstore/issues/19/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/issues/4302","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/issues/4302/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/issues/4302/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/issues/4302/events","html_url":"https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/issues/4302","id":4491087946,"node_id":"I_kwDODfYWS88AAAABC7CQSg","number":4302,"title":"🐛 [Bug]: Doc: generic Query function mentioned but not exist really","user":{"login":"thomasguo","id":10971105,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwOTcxMTA1","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/10971105?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/thomasguo","html_url":"https://github.com/thomasguo","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thomasguo/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thomasguo/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thomasguo/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thomasguo/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thomasguo/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thomasguo/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thomasguo/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thomasguo/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/thomasguo/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id"