eted":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Bug Description\n\nI noticed when uploading multipart form data no error seems to be returned other than \"error\" if the BodyLimit is reached. Below is console log from js POST request of multipart form data. Below is some reproducible sample code.\n\n<img width=\"117\" height=\"43\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e51dc2b0-7392-4e98-8bff-8225410013c2\" />\n\nThe code works fine if you attempt to upload with json: `curl -X POST -d @/some/file localhost:3001/test` it'll return `{\"message\":\"request body greater than limit\"}`, this is expected. But multipart form? only \"error\" and status code is not set.\n\n**Investigated further, the 413 is returned back to chromium based browsers but it is not returned to firefox.**\n\n### How to Reproduce\n\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\n1. Upload a multipart form file that is greater than the BodyLimit.\n2. Observe the request in browser dev tools, it does not return a response, only \"error\".\n\n\n\n### Expected Behavior\n\nWhen uploading multipart form data and BodyLimit is reached custom ErrorHandlers should return the custom handler definition/status code.\n\n### Fiber Version\n\n3.2 and 3.1\n\n### Code Snippet (optional)\n\n```go\nSome sample code to reproduce this:\n\n\npackage main\n\nimport (\n\t\"errors\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\n\t\"github.com/gofiber/fiber/v3\"\n\t\"github.com/gofiber/template/html/v3\"\n)\n\nfunc main() {\n\thtmlEngine := html.New(\".\", \"\")\n\n\tapp := fiber.New(fiber.Config{\n\t\tBodyLimit: 1024,\n\t\tViews:     htmlEngine,\n\t\tErrorHandler: func(c fiber.Ctx, err error) error {\n\t\t\tcode := fiber.StatusInternalServerError\n\n\t\t\t// Retrieve the custom status code if it's a *fiber.Error\n\t\t\tvar e *fiber.Error\n\t\t\tif errors.As(err, &e) {\n\t\t\t\tcode = e.Code\n\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\tswitch code {\n\t\t\tcase fiber.StatusRequestEntityTooLarge:\n\t\t\t\tfmt.Println(\"request body greater than limit\")\n\n\t\t\t\tc.Set(fiber.HeaderContentType, fiber.MIMEApplicationJSON)\n\n\t\t\t\treturn c.Status(fiber.StatusRequestEntityTooLarge).JSON(fiber.Map{\n\t\t\t\t\t\"message\": \"request body greater than limit\",\n\t\t\t\t})\n\t\t\tdefault:\n\t\t\t\treturn c.Status(code).SendString(err.Error())\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t},\n\t})\n\n\tapp.Get(\"/\", func(c fiber.Ctx) error {\n\t\treturn c.Status(fiber.StatusOK).Render(\"test.html\", fiber.Map{})\n\t})\n\n\tapp.Post(\"/\", func(c fiber.Ctx) error {\n\t\tif !c.IsMultipart() {\n\t\t\treturn c.JSON(fiber.Map{\n\t\t\t\t\"message\": \"expect multipart/form\",\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tform, err := c.MultipartForm()\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn c.JSON(fiber.Map{\n\t\t\t\t\"message\": err.Error(),\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tfmt.Printf(\"form: %+v\", form)\n\n\t\treturn c.Status(fiber.StatusOK).SendString(\"got it\")\n\t})\n\n\tapp.Post(\"/test\", func(c fiber.Ctx) error {\n\t\treturn c.SendString(\"ok\")\n\t})\n\n\tapp.Listen(\":3001\", fiber.ListenConfig{})\n}\n\n\n\nhtml:\n\n\n<!doctype html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n    <form id=\"test\" method=\"post\" enctype=\"multipart/form-data\">\n        <div class=\"mb-3\">\n            <label for=\"test\">test</label>\n            <input type=\"file\" id=\"test\" name=\"test\">\n        </div>\n\n        <button type=\"submit\">Upload</button>\n    </form>\n</html>\n```\n\n### Checklist:\n\n- [x] I agree to follow Fiber's [Code of Conduct](https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/blob/main/.github/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md).\n- [x] I have checked for existing issues that describe my problem prior to opening this one.\n- [x] I understand that improperly formatted bug reports may be closed without explanation.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/issues/4236/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":1},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/issues/4236/tim