nes/18/labels","id":16038566,"node_id":"MI_kwDODfYWS84A9Lqm","number":18,"title":"v3.3.0","description":"https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/releases/tag/v3.3.0","creator":{"login":"ReneWerner87","id":7063188,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjcwNjMxODg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7063188?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87","html_url":"https://github.com/ReneWerner87","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"open_issues":0,"closed_issues":80,"state":"closed","created_at":"2026-05-22T07:29:39Z","updated_at":"2026-05-22T07:48:34Z","due_on":"2026-05-22T00:00:00Z","closed_at":"2026-05-22T07:33:01Z"},"comments":6,"created_at":"2026-04-03T05:48:18Z","updated_at":"2026-05-22T07:39:59Z","closed_at":"2026-04-29T09:09:12Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Summary\n\nI've built **[fibersse](https://github.com/vinod-morya/fibersse)** — a production-grade SSE library built natively for Fiber v3. I'd like to propose adding it (or a version of it) to `gofiber/contrib` as the official SSE package.\n\n## The Problem\n\nThere is **no SSE package** in gofiber/contrib today. Every Fiber project that needs Server-Sent Events hand-rolls the same `SendStreamWriter` + `w.Flush()` pattern. Existing Go SSE libraries (`r3labs/sse`, `tmaxmax/go-sse`) are built on `net/http` and **break on Fiber** because:\n\n- `fasthttp.RequestCtx.Done()` only fires on server shutdown, not per-client disconnect\n- The `fasthttpadaptor` creates zombie subscribers that leak memory forever\n- This is confirmed in Fiber issue #3307 and #4145\n\n## What fibersse Provides\n\n| Feature | Status |\n|---------|--------|\n| Fiber v3 native (`SendStreamWriter`) | ✅ |\n| Client disconnect via `w.Flush()` error + heartbeat | ✅ |\n| Hub pattern (single goroutine, topic-based routing) | ✅ |\n| Event coalescing (last-writer-wins per key) | ✅ |\n| 3 priority lanes (Instant / Batched / Coalesced) | ✅ |\n| NATS-style topic wildcards (`*` and `>`) | ✅ |\n| Adaptive per-connection throttling | ✅ |\n| Connection groups (publish by metadata) | ✅ |\n| Built-in JWT + ticket auth helpers | ✅ |\n| Prometheus metrics endpoint | ✅ |\n| Last-Event-ID replay (pluggable) | ✅ |\n| Graceful Kubernetes-style drain | ✅ |\n| Event TTL | ✅ |\n| Auto fan-out from Redis/NATS | ✅ |\n| Zero deps beyond Fiber v3 | ✅ |\n| 29 tests, MIT license | ✅ |\n\n## Links\n\n- **Repository**: https://github.com/vinod-morya/fibersse\n- **Go Docs**: https://pkg.go.dev/github.com/vinod-morya/fibersse\n- **Install**: `go get github.com/vinod-morya/fibersse@v0.1.0`\n\n## Usage Example\n\n```go\nhub := fibersse.New(fibersse.HubConfig{\n    FlushInterval: 2 * time.Second,\n    OnConnect: func(c fiber.Ctx, conn *fibersse.Connection) error {\n        conn.Topics = []string{\"notifications\", \"live\"}\n        return nil\n    },\n})\napp.Get(\"/events\", hub.Handler())\n\nhub.Publish(fibersse.Event{\n    Type:   \"notification\",\n    Data:   map[string]string{\"title\": \"Hello\"},\n    Topics: []string{\"notifications\"},\n})\n```\n\n## Proposal\n\nI'm happy to:\n1. Contribute `fibersse` directly to `gofiber/contrib` as a new `sse` package\n2. Adapt the API to match contrib conventions\n3. Maintain it as part of the contrib ecosystem\n\nWould love to hear from the maintainers on whether this fits the contrib vision and what changes would be needed.\n\ncc @efectn @ReneWerner87","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/issues/4194/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":1},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/issues/4194/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/contrib/issues/1903","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/contrib","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/contrib/issues/1903/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/contrib/issues/1903/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/contrib/issues/1903/events","html_url":"https://github.com/gofiber/contrib/issues/1903","id":4398195842,"node_id":"I_kwDOFYz4tc8AAAABBickgg","number":1903,"title":"🐛 [Bug]: SocketIO middleware is not compatible with socket.io-client","user":{"login":"oSethoum","id":88779394,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjg4Nzc5Mzk0","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/88779394?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/oSethoum","html_url":"https://github.com/oSethoum","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/oSethoum/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/oSethoum/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/oSethoum/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/oSethoum/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/oSethoum/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/oSethoum/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/oSethoum/repos","eve