h is the example from gofiber recipes.\n3. Run `client/index.ts` \n\n\n### Expected Behavior\n\nExpected the middleware to be fully compatible with socket.io\n\n### Contrib package Version\n\nv1.1.3\n\n### Checklist:\n\n- [x] I agree to follow Fiber's [Code of Conduct](https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/blob/master/.github/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md).\n- [x] I have checked for existing issues that describe my problem prior to opening this one.\n- [x] I understand that improperly formatted bug reports may be closed without explanation.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/contrib/issues/1903/reactions","total_count":2,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":2},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/contrib/issues/1903/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/issues/4263","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/issues/4263/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/issues/4263/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/issues/4263/events","html_url":"https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/issues/4263","id":4412161919,"node_id":"I_kwDODfYWS88AAAABBvw_fw","number":4263,"title":"🐛 [Bug]: docs claim `RequestCtx.Done` closes on client disconnect, but it only closes on server shutdown","user":{"login":"gtoxlili","id":39382699,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM5MzgyNjk5","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/39382699?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/gtoxlili","html_url":"https://github.com/gtoxlili","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gtoxlili/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gtoxlili/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gtoxlili/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gtoxlili/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gtoxlili/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gtoxlili/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gtoxlili/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gtoxlili/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/gtoxlili/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":2064310319,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwyMDY0MzEwMzE5","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/labels/%E2%98%A2%EF%B8%8F%20Bug","name":"☢️ Bug","color":"e11d21","default":false,"description":""},{"id":3947514349,"node_id":"LA_kwDODfYWS87rSknt","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/labels/v3","name":"v3","color":"436eee","default":false,"description":""}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/milestones/18","html_url":"https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/milestone/18","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/milestones/18/labels","id":16038566,"node_id":"MI_kwDODfYWS84A9Lqm","number":18,"title":"v3.3.0","description":"https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/releases/tag/v3.3.0","creator":{"login":"ReneWerner87","id":7063188,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjcwNjMxODg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7063188?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87","html_url":"https://github.com/ReneWerner87","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"open_issues":0,"closed_issues":80,"state":"closed","created_at":"2026-05-22T07:29:39Z","updated_at":"2026-05-22T07:48:34Z","due_on":"2026-05-22T00:00:00Z","closed_at":"2026-05-22T07:33:01Z"},"comments":3,"created_at":"2026-05-09T10:20:14Z","updated_at":"2026-05-22T07:38:26Z","closed_at":"2026-05-09T11:37:49Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Bug Description\n\nThe v3 guide [`Go Context`](https://docs.gofiber.io/next/guide/go-context/)  tells readers that `RequestCtx.Done()` fires when the client TCP connection is closed. That is not what fasthttp actually does — `s.done` is only closed when the server itself shuts down. This wording will mislead anyone trying to detect client disconnects from a Fiber handler.\n\n**Quoted text (lines ~100–104):**\n\n> `fasthttpctx` enables `fasthttp` to satisfy the `context.Context` interface.\n> `Deadline` always reports no deadline, `Done` is closed when the client\n> connection ends, and once it fires `Err` reports `context.Canceled`. This\n> means handlers can detect client disconnects while still passing\n> `c.RequestCtx()` into APIs that expect a `context.Context`.\n\n**Quoted text (Summary bullet, lines ~263–264):**\n\n> - `RequestCtx` exposes the raw `fasthttp` context, whose `Done` channel closes\n>   when the client connection ends.\n\n**What fasthttp actually does** — [`server.go#L2925-L2944` in valyala/fasthttp](https://github.com/valyala/fasthttp/blob/master/server.go#L2925-L2944):\n\n```go\n// Note: Because creating a new channel for every request is just too expensive, so\n// RequestCtx.s.done is only closed when the server is shutting down.\nfunc (ctx *RequestCtx) Done() <-chan struct{} {\n    return ctx.s.done\n}\n\n// ...\n// Canceled if the context was canceled (via server Shutdown)\n// or DeadlineExceeded if the context's deadline passed.\n//\n// Note: Because creating a new channel for every request is just too expensive, so\n// RequestCtx.s.done is only closed when the server is shutting down.\nfunc (ctx *RequestCtx) Err() error { ... }\n```\n\n`s.done` is the **server-wide** done channel (allocated once in `Server.Serve`, closed once in `Server.Shutdown`). It is shared by every in-flight request and never carries per-connection cancellation. The fasthttp source comment is unambiguous on this point.\n\nThis is also confirmed publicly by both fasthttp and Fiber maintainers:\n\n- valyala/fasthttp#468 — erikdubbelboer: *\"this is not possible and would be really hard to add\"*\n- valyala/fasthttp#771 — SSE disconnect detection only via `Flush()` error\n- valyala/fasthttp#965 — *\"fasthttp doesn't do any operations on the socket while your handler is running, this is impossible for us to implement\"*\n- gofiber/fiber#805 — Fenny: *\"I'm afraid that is not possible nor efficient with fasthttp sync.pool design\"*, recommends timeout middleware as the only general fallback\n\nSo the documentation paragraph describes behavior that does not exist in any released version of fasthttp.\n\n### How to Reproduce\n\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\n1. Go to https://docs.gofiber.io/docs/core/guide/context#working-with-requestctx-and-fasthttpctx\n2. Read the paragraph stating ``Done` is closed when the client connection ends`.\n3. Run the snippet below: kill the client mid-request and observe that `<-c.RequestCtx().Done()` never fires until the server itself begins shutdown.\n\n### Expected Behavior\n\nThe two passages should describe the actual fasthttp semantics. Suggested replacement (feel free to reword):\n\n> `fasthttpctx` lets `fasthttp.RequestCtx` satisfy the `context.Context` interface. `Deadline` always reports no deadline. **`Done` is shared across all in-flight requests and only closes when the server is shutting down (via `Server.Shutdown`); it does not signal an individual client disconnect.** `Err` returns `context.Canceled` after that channel is closed. Handlers cannot rely on this channel to detect a client TCP disconnect — that is not currently supported by `fasthttp` (see [valyala/fasthttp#468](https://github.com/valyala/fasthttp/issues/468), [#965](https://github.com/valyala/fasthttp/issues/965)). For long-running handlers, wrap the request in a timeout (e.g. `context.WithTimeout` middleware) instead.\n\nThe Summary bullet should be updated to match.\n\n### Fiber Version\n\nv3.x (current docs)\n\n### Code Snippet (optional)\n\n```go\npackage main\n\nimport (\n    \"fmt\"\n    \"log\"\n    \"time\"\n\n    \"github.com/gofiber/fiber/v3\"\n)\n\nfunc main() {\n    app := fiber.New()\n\n    app.Get(\"/wait\", func(c fiber.Ctx) error {\n        fctx := c.RequestCtx()\n        select {\n        case <-fctx.Done():\n            // The docs claim this fires when the client disconnects.\n            // It does not — this branch is only reached on server shutdown.\n            fmt.Println(\"done fired:\", fctx.Err())\n        case <-time.After(30 * time.Second):\n            fmt.Println(\"timed out — client disconnect was never observed\")\n        }\n        return nil\n    })\n\n    log.Fatal(app.Listen(\":3000\"))\n}\n```\n\nReproduction:\n\n```bash\n# Terminal A\ngo run main.go\n\n# Terminal B\ncurl http://localhost:3000/wait &\nCURL_PID=$!\nsleep 1\nkill -9 $CURL_PID   # close the client TCP connection\n# Server still prints \"timed out — client disconnect was never observed\".\n```\n\n### Checklist:\n\n- [x] I agree to follow Fiber's [Code of Conduct](https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/blob/main/.github/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md).\n- [x] I have checked for existing issues that describe my problem prior to opening this one.\n- [x] I understand that improperly formatted bug reports may be closed without explanation.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/issues/4263/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/issues/4263/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/issues/4217","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/issues/4217/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/issues/4217/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/issues/4217/events","html_url":"https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/issues/4217","id":4274027127,"node_id":"I_kwDODfYWS87-wHp3","number":4217,"title":"🤗 [Question]: The domain is expired. You need to renew again.","user":{"login":"kresnasatya","id":11099186,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjExMDk5MTg2","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/11099186?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/kresnasatya","html_url":"https://github.com/kresnasatya","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kresnasatya/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kresnasatya/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kresnasatya/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kresnasatya/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kresnasatya/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kresnasatya/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kresnasatya/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kresnasatya/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kresnasatya/received_events","type":"User","user_view