l":"https://api.github.com/users/To-be-w1th0ut/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/To-be-w1th0ut/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/To-be-w1th0ut/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/To-be-w1th0ut/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/To-be-w1th0ut/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/To-be-w1th0ut/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/To-be-w1th0ut/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/To-be-w1th0ut/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/To-be-w1th0ut/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":true,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":4,"created_at":"2026-04-28T10:34:06Z","updated_at":"2026-04-28T12:02:10Z","closed_at":"2026-04-28T11:54:24Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":"spam","sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"# Ghost Bits Vulnerability in Fiber Framework\n\n## Summary\n\nA critical security vulnerability has been identified in Go's type conversion mechanism that affects Fiber applications. The vulnerability, dubbed \"Ghost Bits,\" enables attackers to bypass WAF detection and execute SQL injection, path traversal, XSS, and command injection attacks by exploiting silent high-bit truncation during type conversions from `rune` (32-bit) to `byte` (8-bit).\n\n## Severity\n\n**Critical** - CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H (9.8)\n\n## Affected Components\n\n- Fiber routing and parameter handling\n- Fiber context query parameters\n- Fiber form data processing\n\n## Affected Versions\n\nAll versions\n\n## Technical Details\n\n### Vulnerability Mechanism\n\nWhen Go code converts a `rune` (32-bit Unicode code point) to `byte` (8-bit), the high 24 bits are silently discarded:\n\n```go\nvar ch rune = '\\u2F58'  // 爻 (U+2F58) = 0x00002F58\nb := byte(ch)           // Only low 8 bits: 0x58 = 'X'\n```\n\nThis silent truncation creates a **65,536x attack space** compared to Java's 8-bit truncation.\n\n### Attack Example\n\n**SQL Injection Bypass**:\n\n```go\n// Original payload: ' OR '1'='1\n// Ghost Bits payload: ħ OR ħ1ħ=ħ1\n\n// WAF sees: \"ħ OR ħ1ħ=ħ1\" (no match)\n// Backend converts: ħ (U+0127) → 0x27 = '\n// Result: \"' OR '1'='1\" (SQL injection executed)\n```\n\n### Proof of Concept\n\n```go\npackage main\n\nimport (\n    \"github.com/gofiber/fiber/v2\"\n    \"strings\"\n)\n\nfunc main() {\n    app := fiber.New()\n    \n    app.Get(\"/user\", func(c *fiber.Ctx) error {\n        id := c.Query(\"id\")\n        wafPattern := \"' OR '1'='1\"\n        \n        // WAF detection\n        if !strings.Contains(id, wafPattern) {\n            // WAF bypass successful\n        }\n        \n        // Backend processing (vulnerable code)\n        var idBytes []byte\n        for _, ch := range id {\n            idBytes = append(idBytes, byte(ch))\n        }\n        \n        restored := string(idBytes)\n        if restored == wafPattern {\n            return c.JSON(fiber.Map{\"message\": \"SQL injection successful\"})\n        }\n        return c.JSON(fiber.Map{\"message\": \"Safe\"})\n    })\n    \n    app.Listen(\":8080\")\n}\n```\n\n## Impact\n\nAttackers can bypass WAF/IDS protection and execute:\n- SQL injection\n- Path traversal\n- XSS\n- Command injection\n- File upload bypass\n\n## Mitigation\n\n### Immediate Mitigation\n\n1. **Avoid dangerous type conversions**:\n   ```go\n   // ❌ Dangerous\n   for _, ch := range s {\n       b := byte(ch)\n   }\n   \n   // ✅ Safe\n   bytes := []byte(s)\n   ```\n\n2. **Input validation**:\n   ```go\n   func validateInput(s string) bool {\n       for _, ch := range s {\n           if ch > 127 {\n               return false\n           }\n       }\n       return true\n   }\n   ```\n\n3. **Use parameterized queries**:\n   ```go\n   // ❌ Dangerous\n   db.Exec(fmt.Sprintf(\"SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = '%s'\", id))\n   \n   // ✅ Safe\n   db.Query(\"SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ?\", id)\n   ```\n\n## References\n\n- Go Security Advisory: https://github.com/golang/go/issues/78989\n- Original Research: Ghost Bits Vulnerability\n- Black Hat Asia 2026: \"Cast Attack: A New Threat Posed by Ghost Bits in Java\"\n\n---\n**This vulnerability has been disclosed following responsible disclosure practices.**","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/issues/4244/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/issues/4244/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/issues/4234","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/issues/4234/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/issues/4234/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/issues/4234/events","html_url":"https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/issues/4234","id":4329075103,"node_id":"I_kwDODfYWS88AAAABAghxnw","number":4234,"title":"🐛 [Bug]: Query Extractor Failing","user":{"login":"djamez","id":30546705,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMwNTQ2NzA1","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/30546705?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/djamez","html_url":"https://github.com/djamez","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/djamez/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/djamez/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/djamez/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/djamez/starred{/owner}{/r