0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Bug Description\n\nThe `compress` middleware depends on Fiber’s `etag` package to recompute strong ETags after compressing the response body. That etag code uses `math.MaxUint32`, which overflows int on 32-bit, crashing with an `math.MaxUint32 (untyped int constant 4294967295) overflows int` error.\nCurrently the only solution I've found is conditional compilation with build tags, avoiding the `compress` dependency (which in turn uses `etag`) on building binaries targeted to 32 bit systems.\nThere was already a PR trying to fix this which was closed: https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/pull/3469\n\n### How to Reproduce\n\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\n1. Try to build an app using the `compress` middleware to a 32 bit executable.\n\n### Expected Behavior\n\nThe Fiber app using the `compress` middleware should build with no errors 32 bit apps.\n\n### Fiber Version\n\nv3.1.0\n\n### Code Snippet (optional)\n\n```go\n\n```\n\n### Checklist:\n\n- [x] I agree to follow Fiber's [Code of Conduct](https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/blob/main/.github/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md).\n- [x] I have checked for existing issues that describe my problem prior to opening this one.\n- [x] I understand that improperly formatted bug reports may be closed without explanation.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/issues/4134/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":1},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/issues/4134/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/guanchuan1314/vow/issues/931","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/guanchuan1314/vow","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/guanchuan1314/vow/issues/931/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/guanchuan1314/vow/issues/931/comments","events_